</div>
			<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Mervyn King (judge)</h1>
									<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">
									<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><table class="infobox biography vcard" style="width:22em">
<tr>
<th colspan="2" style="text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold"><span class="fn">Mervyn Mau E. King</span></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Born</th>
<td><span class="nickname">Mervyn Masiapa Mau Eldred King</span><br />
<span style="display:none">(<span class="bday">1937-07-22</span>)</span> 22 July 1937 <span class="noprint ForceAgeToShow">(age&#160;77)</span><br />
<span class="birthplace"><a href="/wiki/Johannesburg" title="Johannesburg">Johannesburg</a></span></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Nationality</th>
<td class="category">South African</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Occupation</th>
<td class="role">Attorney, arbitrator, mediator, commission chair</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<th scope="row">Known&#160;for</th>
<td><a href="/wiki/King_Report_on_Corporate_Governance" title="King Report on Corporate Governance">King Report on Corporate Governance</a></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p><b>Mervyn Eldred King</b> (born 22 July 1937, <a href="/wiki/Johannesburg" title="Johannesburg">Johannesburg</a>)<sup id="cite_ref-who_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-who-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> is a South African corporate attorney, <a href="/wiki/Arbitration" title="Arbitration">arbitrator</a>, <a href="/wiki/Mediation" title="Mediation">mediator</a>, corporate director, commission chair, author and speaker. A former judge of the <a href="/wiki/Supreme_Court_of_South_Africa" title="Supreme Court of South Africa">Supreme Court of South Africa</a>, he is currently chairman of the IIRC, chairman emeritus of the <a href="/wiki/Global_Reporting_Initiative" title="Global Reporting Initiative">Global Reporting Initiative</a> and director of the Association of Business Administrators of Southern Africa. He is best known for chairing the <a href="/wiki/King_Report_on_Corporate_Governance" title="King Report on Corporate Governance">King Committee on Corporate Governance</a>, which issued three comprehensive reports in 1994, 2002 and 2009 endorsing an integrated and inclusive approach to <a href="/wiki/Corporate_governance" title="Corporate governance">corporate governance</a> in South Africa.<sup id="cite_ref-doc_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-doc-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
